Argo-CD is an optional tool to deploy micro service application automatically into K8S cluster for any commit changes. 
See official link for more information:
https://argo-cd.readthedocs.io/en/stable/core_concepts/

# create an argo-cd application. Important fields to input:

https://argo-cd.readthedocs.io/en/stable/getting_started/

key-fields:

1. General

2. Source

3. Destination

4. Select Helm in drop box and add
  VALUES FILES=values.yaml

then click CREATE

# key fields:
PROJECT
CLUSTER: https://kubernetes.default.svc
# target namespace on K8S cluster
NAMESPACE
# repo url shall be git server or on storage server that stores HELM package
REPO URL
TARGET REVISION (git sha)
PATH: eg chart
